data.name: textBox2.Text
data.value:
This Wizard test application demonstates the basic functionality of the Wizard control.
Here are just some of Wizard's amazing features: 1) Multiple execution paths of pages may be taken by handling the BackButtonPressed and NextButtonPressed events. 2) Many design-time features including new page wizards, page navigation, and go to page functionality. 3) Completely modify the appearance of the Wizard by using different background fills or creating a custom renderer. 4) Two modes of page sequencing. 5) The Wizard control may be placed on a resizable Form. While this is not generally done, it can be a useful feature in some cases. If you do choose to use a resizable form, make sure the pages' child controls can resize.

data.name: label11.Text
data.value: In design-mode, properties have been set on this page so that when this page is selected, the Back and Next buttons are initially disabled. Then some quick processing occurs and the buttons are re-enabled programmatically. See the SelectionChanged event for this code.

data.name: label10.Text
data.value: This page is the finish page for the first execution path of the Wizard. Back up two pages and choose the second execution path to see a different finish page. Or press the button below to jump right to the second execution path.

data.name: label20.Text
data.value: Each of these background fills are programmatically created and set. You can also set up all the background fills in the designer. Use Wizard's powerful custom appearance features to make your Wizards follow your creative vision.
